The paper deals with the language equivalence problem of deterministic one-counter automata, which is a topic in formal languages and automata theory. Therefore, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely sub-category. The problem is also related to computational complexity, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as another likely sub-category. The paper uses techniques from logic and graph theory, which are topics in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also involves the use of data structures, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses the use of information theory, which is a topic in cs.IT (Information Theory).
